SPECIFICATION AUTHORITY
-----------------------

This repository is a clean-room TypeScript implementation of the MCP
"Task-Based Access Control" (TBAC) Standards Enhancement Proposal, revision
r41 (2026-04-21). r41 is a documentation/submission-readiness revision
wire-compatible with r40 (2026-04-20); both revisions MUST interoperate
per §Preamble P2.1. The normative source of truth for protocol semantics
is the file `spec/0000-tbac-task-based-access-control-r41.md` in this
repository.

PATENT NON-ASSERTION
--------------------

Hawcx Inc. has filed patent applications covering implementation techniques
for signcryption constructions, TQS architecture optimizations, Assembler
architecture, and bidirectional response encryption mechanisms (see the
SEP "Patent notice" section at the bottom of `spec/0000-tbac-task-
based-access-control-r41.md`).

The normative requirements of the SEP — the token format, privilege
classifier schema, verification cascade interface, capability negotiation,
and `_meta` transport — are described at the interface level and do not
require the use of patented methods.

Consistent with the SEP's own commitment, Hawcx Inc. commits to not
asserting patent claims against implementations that conform solely to
the SEP's normative requirements. For patent-related inquiries, contact:
legal@hawcx.com.

CLEAN-ROOM BOUNDARY
-------------------

This implementation was built from the SEP document alone. It does not
incorporate, port, or reference any source code, type definitions, test
vectors, or proprietary constants from Hawcx's HAAP (`haap-*`) codebase.
Every domain-separation label in this repository uses the `tbac-*` prefix
normative to §A.5 and §12.2.
